HEADWORD: Wellhead
<hw>Well"head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A source, spring,
or fountain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At the <qex>wellhead</qex> the purest streams arise.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our public-school and university life is a great
<qex>wellhead</qex> of new and irresponsible words.</q>
<rj><qau>Earle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wellhole</ent>⟦br⟧
